Write a Java program to create a generic method that takes two lists of the same type
and merges them into a single list. This method alternates the elements of each list.
Output:
List of Numbers:
[1, 3, 6, 7]
[9, 4, 2, 8]
Unsorted Number list is : [1, 9, 3, 4, 6, 2, 7, 8]
Merged and Sorted Numbers:
[1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9]
List of Colors:
[Red, Green, Blue]
[White, Black, Orange, Pink]
Merged and Sorted Colors:
[Black, Blue, Green, Orange, Pink, Red, White]
